<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41107b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41107b">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41107b"> 107(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Persian jeweller = / English tailor</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Said <i>ironic&egrave;</i>, the <mark>jeweller</mark> being held to be one of the dishonest classes, like the washerman, the water-carrier, the gardener, etc. <mark>In England we may find his representative</mark> in the &ldquo;silversmith,&rdquo; who will ask a pound sterling for a bit of metal which cost him perhaps five shillings or even less, and who hates to be bought by weight <small> Richard F. Burton, trans. <a name="RBTE3" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE3"><cite title="source">Supplemental Nights to the Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) V, 21n1</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
